steps:
  title: Our Process
  intro: 'Our approach ensures seamless alignment with your business objectives through a structured, two-stage process:'
  title_outcomes: 'Outcomes:'
  title_what: 'What we do?'
steps_elements:
  stage_1:
    label: Stage 1
    name: Plan
    steps:
      step_1:
        label: Step 1
        title: Perform a Metrics Audit
        content: |-
          We evaluate your existing metrics, identify gaps, and define the desired outcome of our collaboration. To validate our key learnings, we run a Minimum Viable Product (MVP).
        outcomes:
          - Identification of metrics gaps
          - A catalog of required data metrics
          - A maturity score of your data landscape
          - A functional MVP to demonstrate value
      step_2:
        label: Step 2
        title: Create a Roadmap
        content: |-
          We translate the benchmark into a detailed roadmap, outlining the resources, IT infrastructure, and steps required to achieve your data goals.
        outcomes:
          - A comprehensive data marts roadmap
          - Identification of domain owners
          - A resource plan for successful execution
          - Infrastructure review and recommendations
  stage_2:
    label: Stage 2
    name: Execution
    steps:
      step_3:
        label: Step 3
        title: Release Metrics & Reports
        content: |-
          Through iterative sprints, our analysts develop the agreed-upon data metrics and reports. We validate the outputs, align them with stakeholders, and onboard your teams.
        outcomes:
          - Unified metrics
          - Standardized reports ready for use
          - Aligned outputs with organizational needs
          - Onboarded users, prepared to leverage the new insights
      step_4:
        label: Step 4
        title: Operationalize and Support
        content: |-
          We transition the developed marts and reports to operations, ensuring they are run, monitored, and supported seamlessly.
        outcomes:
          - Handover to operational teams
          - Continued technical and strategic support
          - Reliable, scalable systems to power ongoing insights
          - Comprehensive training and documentation

why:
  title: Why Our Process Work
  intro: |-
    Our methodology has been tested over many years and use cases, and it works thanks to these key pillars:
why_elements:
  - title: Standards
    content: We have data marts building blocks in domains such as sales, purchasing, inventory, and production, ensuring we move faster and avoid asking basic questions.
  - title: Cross-Functional
    content: Our teams are cross-functional and can work with both IT and business at the same time.
  - title: Outcome Based
    content: We are focused on the outcome, which is unified metrics for your business, and not on consuming development days.

faq:
  title: FAQ
  intro: |-
    Curious to know more? Schedule a call and get all your questions answered!
  cta:_label: Let’s talk
  cta_target: https://meetings-eu1.hubspot.com/alessio-civitillo/book-a-call
  items:
    - title: What is the typical steps from initial assessment to project kick-off?
      content: |-
        - Planning Phase: Typically takes 8-12 weeks, depending on schedules.
        - Execution Phase: Ranges from 6 to 24 months, depending on the approved scope and complexity.
    - title: How much involvement is required from my team?
      content: |-
        - Planning Phase: Approximately 20 hours per involved executive over the 8-12 weeks.
        - Execution Phase:
            - ~2 hours per week per data owner
            - ~2 hours per week per subject-matter expert
            - ~2 hours per week for the steering committee
    - title: When can we expect to see the first data marts and reports?
      content: |-
        - We deliver a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) during the first step of the planning phase.
        - Initial outcomes can be seen from 3 to 12 weeks after the collaboration kick-off.
    - title: Who from my team should be involved in the project?
      content: |-
        - Executives to provide strategic direction
        - Data owners to ensure access and alignment
        - Subject-matter experts (SMEs) for domain-specific insights
        - Steering committee members for oversight and decision-making
    - title: What industries and domains does dyvenia specialize in?
      content: |-
        - We specialize in manufacturing with expertise in:
            - Finance
            - Performance management
            - Sales and operations
    - title: Does my organization need a certain level of data maturity to work with dyvenia?
      content: |-
        - No. Our solutions are tailored to meet you where you are and help elevate your data maturity, whether you’re just beginning or refining your approach.
    - title: Can you integrate with our existing tools and technology stack?
      content: |-
        - Yes. We design our solutions to seamlessly fit into any architecture and tech stack, ensuring compatibility and minimal disruption to your workflows.
    - title: Can we engage with dyvenia only for Phase 1 of the process?
      content: |-
        - Yes. You can choose to work with us only on the planning phase.
        - We focus on auditing your metrics, identifying gaps, creating a tailored roadmap, and delivering an MVP.
        - This phase delivers valuable insights and a clear action plan, whether or not you proceed to the execution phase with us.
    - title: How much does a typical project cost?
      content: |-
        - Phase 1: €45,000. If you’re not satisfied, we offer a full refund of all invoices.
        - Phase 2: Scoping during planning determines the budget.
        - For a mid-sized team, costs typically average ~€50,000 per month.

blog:
  intro: Selected Articles. Check our blog for more.
  title: Our Insights
---

<header class="section page-header">
  {% svg "divider/soft-top-bubble", null, "seperator small" %}

  {% if hero.image %}
    {% image hero.image, "", null, "eager" %}
  {% endif %}

  <div class="section__inner region region-space-xl">
    <div class="wrapper flow">
      <h1>{{ hero.title }}</h1>
      {{ hero.subtitle | markdownFormat | safe }}
      <a href="{{ hero.button_target }}" class="button flow-space-l">
        {{ hero.button_text }} {% svg "misc/arrow" %}</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="intro | wrapper">
  <header class="header | region flow prose">
    <h2 class="text-step-3">{{ intro.title1 }} <span>{{ intro.title2 }}</span></h2>
    {{ intro.content | markdownFormat | safe }}
  </header>
</div>

<div class="what | wrapper">
  <article class="feature region  grid" data-layout="50-50">
    <div class="flow">
      <h2 class="text-step-2">{{ what_are.title }}</h2>
      {{ what_are.content | markdownFormat | safe }}
      <a href="{{ what_are.button_target }}" class="button flow-space-l" data-ghost-button>
        {{ what_are.button_text }} {% svg "misc/arrow" %}</a
      >
    </div>
    {% image what_are.image, what_are.image_alt %}
  </article>
</div>

<section class="steps | wrapper region" aria-labelledby="steps-title">
  <div class="feature">
    <header id="steps-title" class="header | flow">
      <h2 class="text-step-3">{{ steps.title }}</h2>
      <p>{{ steps.intro }}</p>
    </header>

    <div class="tabs mt-2xl">
      <nav aria-label="Process Stages">
        <ul class="arrows | repel" role="list">
          {% for stageKey, stage in steps_elements %}
            <li>
              <h3><span>{{ stage.label }}</span> {{ stage.name }}</h3>
              <ul class="cluster" role="tablist">
                {% for stepKey, step in stage.steps %}
                  <li role="presentation">
                    <span class="step-number" aria-hidden="true">{{ step.label.slice(5) }}</span>
                    <button
                      id="tab-{{ stepKey }}"
                      role="tab"
                      data-tab-target="panel-{{ stepKey }}"
                      aria-controls="panel-{{ stepKey }}"
                      aria-selected="{% if loop.first %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"
                      class="button"
                    >
                      <span class="step-title">{{ step.title }}</span>
                    </button>
                  </li>
                {% endfor %}
              </ul>
            </li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      </nav>

      {% for stageKey, stage in steps_elements %}
        {% for stepKey, step in stage.steps %}
          <div
            tabindex="0"
            id="panel-{{ stepKey }}"
            role="tabpanel"
            data-tab-panel="panel-{{ stepKey }}"
            aria-labelledby="tab-{{ stepKey }}"
          >
            <div class="sidebar mt-xl-2xl">
              <header class="flow">
                <p class="button" data-label>{{ stage.label }} {{ stage.name }}</p>
                <h3 class="flow-space-2xs">{{ step.title }}</h3>
              </header>
              <article class="flow prose">
                <h4>{{ steps.title_what }}</h4>
                <p>{{ step.content }}</p>
                <h4>{{ steps.title_outcomes }}</h4>
                <ul>
                  {% for outcome in step.outcomes %}
                    <li>{{ outcome }}</li>
                  {% endfor %}
                </ul>
              </article>
            </div>
          </div>
        {% endfor %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="why | wrapper">
  <article class="full region flow">
    <header class="header | flow">
      <h2 class="text-step-3">{{ why.title }}</h2>
      <p>{{ why.intro }}</p>
    </header>
    <div class="split mt-xl">
      {% svg "brand/check" %}
      <ol class="timeline">
        {% for key in why_elements %}
          <li>
            <span>{{ loop.index }}</span>
            <div class="flow flow-space-3xs">
              <h3 class="text-step-1">{{ key.title }}</h3>
              <p>{{ key.content }}</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="faq | wrapper region">
  <div class="sidebar feature">
    <div class="flow">
      <h2>{{ faq.title }}</h2>
      <p>{{ faq.intro }}</p>
      <a href="{{ hero.button_target }}" class="button flow-space-l" data-button-variant="blue">
        {{ hero.button_text }} {% svg "misc/arrow" %}</a
      >
    </div>
    <div class="details flow">
      <div class="control | cluster" aria-label="{{ meta.details.aria }}">
        <button id="expandAll" class="button" data-small-button>{{ meta.details.expand }}</button>
        <button id="collapseAll" class="button" data-small-button>{{ meta.details.collapse }}</button>
      </div>
      {%- for item in faq.items -%}
        <details id="{{ item.title | slugify }}" class="prose">
          <summary>{{ item.title }}</summary>
          {{- item.content | markdownFormat | safe -}}
        </details>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper">
  <section class="full | region">
    <div class="wrapper flow prose">
      <h2><a class="no-underline hover:underline" href="/insights/">{{ blog.title }}</a></h2>

      {% if blog.intro %}
        <p>{{ blog.intro }}</p>
      {% endif %}

      <div class="feature">
        <custom-masonry layout="50-50">
        <!-- loop posts -->
        {% set itemList = collections.allPosts %}
        {% asyncEach item in itemList.slice(0, 4) %}
          {% set definedDate = item.date %}
          {% include "partials/card-blog.njk" %}
        {% endeach %}
        </custom-masonry>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

{%- css "inline" -%}
  {%- include 'css/process.css' -%}
  {%- include "css/page-header.css" -%}
  {%- include "css/details.css" -%}
{%- endcss -%}

{% js "defer" %}
  {% include "scripts/details.js" %}
  {% include "scripts/tabs.js" %}
{% endjs %}
